      "issue_body_html": "<h2>Canonical Project Page<\/h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"https://github.com/Thorncrag/ARRP/blob/main/framework/logs/HORIZON_SCAN_LOG.md\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Horizon Scan Log<\/a><\/li><li>Horizon ID: <code>HOR-010<\/code><\/li><li>Intake date: <code>2026-06-25<\/code><\/li><\/ul>\n<h2>Concern<\/h2>\n<p>Immigration-courthouse arrests and courthouse-access chilling after reversal of the sensitive-locations policy.<\/p>\n<h2>Existing Overlap<\/h2>\n<p>DOM-005, DOM-008, A-14 domestic federal law-enforcement concerns; Project 2025 crosswalk notes on immigration-enforcement due process; possible access-to-courts connection to A-04.<\/p>\n<h2>Issue-Admission Result<\/h2>\n<p>Watch pending judicial development; not yet admitted. Current court decisions appear to be carving out limits on executive courthouse arrests, so a statutory proposal may become unnecessary or may need to be narrower.<\/p>\n<h2>New Issue / Merge Recommendation<\/h2>\n<p>Do not create or merge into an issue yet; keep HOR-010 active on the horizon list.<\/p>\n<h2>Current Disposition<\/h2>\n<p>Deferred pending a durable gap, conflict among courts, enforcement evasion, inadequate remedy, or appellate reversal that would justify admission.<\/p>\n<h2>Why this is deferred<\/h2>\n<p>Although additional research and preliminary drafting could proceed now, ARRP is affirmatively postponing further candidate development because active litigation may eliminate, narrow, or materially reshape both the institutional gap and any appropriate statutory remedy. Advancing a proposal before that posture becomes clearer would be premature.<\/p>\n<h2>Reconsideration condition<\/h2>\n<p>Reconsider the deferral when a controlling appellate ruling establishes or rejects a durable access-to-courts protection, when conflicting rulings emerge, or when documented enforcement evasion or an inadequate judicial remedy shows that a statutory gap remains.<\/p>\n<h2>Sources / Next Source Need<\/h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://apnews.com/article/judge-rules-against-immigration-courthouse-arrests-e99e8e3a27647a716917217cc1c207ab\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">AP on court ruling against immigration-courthouse arrests<\/a>. Next source need: district-court order, appellate posture, DHS policy history, and any follow-on enforcement-evasion evidence.<\/p>\n<h2>Confidence<\/h2>\n<p>Medium pending judicial development<\/p>\n<h2>Workflow Note<\/h2>\n<p>This GitHub issue is the public workflow wrapper for the horizon candidate. Use the project-board fields for lifecycle status, workstream, area, and release tracking. The repository remains the substantive record until the item is admitted, merged, deferred, or retired.<\/p>",
