      "issue_body_html": "<h2>Canonical Project Page<\/h2>\n<ul><li>Horizon ID: <code>HOR-023<\/code><\/li><\/ul>\n<h2>Horizon candidate<\/h2>\n<p>ARRP should retain foreign election interference and campaign counterintelligence safeguards as a deferred horizon candidate. The concern includes foreign cyber operations, foreign digital influence operations, hacked-material dissemination, campaign-contact safeguards, politically sensitive counterintelligence predicates, FISA accuracy duties, classified oversight, and election-security coordination.<\/p>\n<h2>Why this is deferred<\/h2>\n<p>This item sits at the intersection of national security, election administration, counterintelligence, FISA, cyber operations, classified oversight, and First Amendment limits. ARRP should not convert it into a developed proposal unless the project later has appropriate subject-matter expertise or a stronger source-development base.<\/p>\n<p>Although source development and preliminary drafting could proceed now, ARRP is affirmatively postponing further candidate development because proceeding without that expertise or evidentiary foundation would risk an overbroad or technically unsound remedy.<\/p>\n<h2>Reconsideration condition<\/h2>\n<p>Reconsider the deferral when ARRP has qualified national-security, election-security, counterintelligence, FISA, cyber, and First Amendment expertise available for an issue-admission review, or when a sufficiently developed primary-source record and narrowly defined remedy question are ready for review by such experts.<\/p>\n<h2>Source-development leads<\/h2>\n<ul><li>Mueller Report / ARRP crosswalk: https://github.com/Thorncrag/ARRP/blob/main/research/mueller-report-arrp-crosswalk.md<\/li><li>Durham Report / ARRP crosswalk: https://github.com/Thorncrag/ARRP/blob/main/research/durham-report-arrp-crosswalk.md<\/li><li>Future primary-source set: Senate Intelligence Committee Russian active-measures reports; the 2017 Intelligence Community Assessment; Internet Research Agency and GRU indictments; DOJ Inspector General Crossfire Hurricane and FISA review materials; FISC orders; FISA reform history; CISA election-security guidance; campaign-contact rules; hacked-material handling rules; and foreign digital influence safeguards.<\/li><\/ul>\n<h2>Candidate homes<\/h2>\n<p>Possible future home: A-02 Election Integrity. Cross-reference source development may also touch DOJ-003, DOJ-007, A-07 Classified Information, A-15 Congressional Oversight, and A-18 Factual Integrity depending on the remedy design.<\/p>\n<h2>Current disposition<\/h2>\n<p>Deferred horizon item pending expert-led issue-admission review. If ARRP later brings on national-security, election-security, counterintelligence, FISA, cyber, and First Amendment expertise, this item could be folded into the project.<\/p>",
