        "decision_date": "2026-07-18",
        "original_concern": "INA section 212(f) may permit broad class-based entry suspensions through generalized detrimental-interest findings without a sufficiently specific statutory nexus, fixed duration, transparent record, or timely review.",
        "decision": "Promoted from preliminary intake INTAKE-GAP-009 to an active Horizon candidate; static HOR ID tracked through GitHub issue #303. Promotion does not admit a proposal or prescribe immigration policy.",
        "integrated_into": "Provisionally A-24; duplicate and boundary review with RIGHTS-002, HOR-037, RET-001, EMERG-001, and JUD-011.",
        "rationale": "Congress deliberately granted broad authority, the Supreme Court has recognized substantial presidential latitude, and some proclamations include findings, exceptions, duration, or periodic review. Representative records include the 2017 entry-suspension order and a 2025 proclamation; 21 directives remain routed as candidate evidence.",
        "follow_up": "Review controlling doctrine and compare safeguards across uses of section 212(f), concrete difficult-to-remedy harm, timely review, and overlap before admission.",
