      "id": "HOR-042",
      "number": 304,
      "title": "Minimum Safeguards for Presidential Statutory Waivers",
      "full_title": "HOR-042: Minimum Safeguards for Presidential Statutory Waivers",
      "issue_state": "Open",
      "development_level": "Candidate",
      "workflow_status": "Development",
      "area": "CONG",
      "priority": "Medium",
      "release_blocker": "Later",
      "last_audit": "Preliminary candidate promotion (2026-07-18)",
      "next_audit": "Build the statute-by-statute waiver safeguard matrix and test cross-statutory remedy fit.",
      "canonical_page": "https://github.com/Thorncrag/ARRP/issues/304",
      "issue_url": "https://github.com/Thorncrag/ARRP/issues/304",
      "labels": [
        "kind: horizon"
      ],
      "needs_monitoring": false,
      "created_at": "2026-07-19T00:43:01Z",
      "updated_at": "2026-07-19T00:43:01Z",
      "issue_body_html": "<h2>Canonical Project Page<\/h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"https://github.com/Thorncrag/ARRP/blob/main/framework/logs/HORIZON_SCAN_LOG.md\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Horizon Scan Log<\/a><\/li><li><a href=\"https://github.com/Thorncrag/ARRP/blob/main/areas/CONG/README.md\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Provisional congressional-power area<\/a><\/li><li>Horizon ID: <code>HOR-042<\/code><\/li><li>Preliminary intake provenance: <code>INTAKE-GAP-010<\/code><\/li><\/ul>\n<h2>Workflow Purpose<\/h2>\n<p>This issue is the public workflow wrapper for an ARRP Horizon candidate concerning minimum safeguards for express presidential statutory waivers. Promotion does not admit a proposal or presume that Congress acted improperly by authorizing any waiver.<\/p>\n<h2>Institutional Question<\/h2>\n<p>Congress may authorize a President to suspend enacted substantive or procedural safeguards through broad or conclusory findings without consistent minimum requirements for reasons, scope, duration, notice, reporting, or review. The candidate asks whether any neutral minimum is warranted across statutes while preserving statute-specific congressional judgments.<\/p>\n<h2>Existing Coverage and Counterargument<\/h2>\n<p>JUD-011 and FUND-001 concern executive departure from congressional mandates; they do not own conduct Congress expressly authorized through a waiver or exception. EMERG-001 is declaration-specific, REG-006 concerns rulemaking and legal positions, and WAR-001 and federalism records may own particular applications. DHS secretary-issued border-wall waivers remain agency-delegation comparators only and do not broaden this candidate&#x27;s presidential-waiver scope.<\/p>\n<p>The strongest counterargument is that Congress deliberately created each waiver and may rationally prefer speed, flexibility, and presidential accountability. Several statutes already include meaningful findings, fixed duration, notice, retained standards, certification, or congressional reporting.<\/p>\n<h2>Supporting Record<\/h2>\n<p>Representative source IDs: <code>SRC-1201<\/code>, <code>SRC-1202<\/code>, <code>SRC-1203<\/code>, <code>SRC-1211<\/code>, <code>SRC-1212<\/code>, <code>SRC-1213<\/code>, <code>SRC-1214<\/code>, <code>SRC-0871<\/code>, <code>SRC-0877<\/code>, <code>SRC-0889<\/code>, <code>SRC-0943<\/code>, <code>SRC-0944<\/code>, <code>SRC-0995<\/code>, and <code>SRC-0996<\/code> in the project source registry. The directive catalog retains the complete supporting cluster.<\/p>\n<h2>Next Step<\/h2>\n<p>Build a statute-by-statute safeguard matrix; identify material waived requirements, existing review and oversight, difficult-to-reverse harm, and whether a cross-statutory floor is legally coherent before recommending admission, merger, or retirement.<\/p>",
