        "rationale": "Congress deliberately created each waiver and may prefer speed and flexibility; several statutes already impose meaningful findings, fixed duration, notice, certification, retained standards, or reporting. Representative records include a 2025 foreign-assistance waiver and a 2026 presidential determination; 26 directives remain routed as candidate evidence.",
        "follow_up": "Build a statute-by-statute safeguard matrix and admit only a neutral cross-statutory remedy that can coexist with Congress's statute-specific judgments.",
