      "issue_body_lines": [
        "## Final Disposition — Integrated into REG-001",
        "",
        "**Decision date:** July 10, 2026  ",
        "**Record finalized:** July 14, 2026",
        "",
        "HOR-018 was integrated into [REG-001](https://github.com/Thorncrag/ARRP/blob/main/areas/REG/issues/REG-001.md) as its lower-review Tier Two source-development lane. The receiving proposal now addresses substantial and sustained executive impairment of congressionally assigned duties through reductions in force, program transfers, funding freezes, system shutdowns, program termination, or administrative nonuse, while distinguishing those acts from ordinary executive policy and management.",
        "",
        "No separate proposal was created. This closed issue and the [Horizon Scan Log](https://github.com/Thorncrag/ARRP/blob/main/framework/logs/HORIZON_SCAN_LOG.md) preserve the permanent intake history. The inactive Project card was removed. The archived intake analysis below is retained for provenance and is superseded by this final disposition.",
        "",
        "---",
        "",
        "## Archived Intake Record",
        "",
        "## Canonical Project Page",
        "",
        "- [Horizon Scan Log](https://github.com/Thorncrag/ARRP/blob/main/framework/logs/HORIZON_SCAN_LOG.md)",
        "- Horizon ID: `HOR-018`",
        "- Intake date: `2026-06-27`",
        "",
        "## Concern",
        "",
        "Unilateral executive dismantling, absorption, or functional nullification of congressionally created agencies, with USAID and the Department of Education as current source-development examples.",
        "",
        "## Existing Overlap",
        "",
        "Primarily [REG-004](https://github.com/Thorncrag/ARRP/blob/main/areas/REG/README.md); related to A-11 funding/appropriations controls, A-08 civil-service/DOGE operational control, A-20 federalism, and A-24 civil-rights administration where specific statutory programs or rights offices are impaired.",
        "",
        "## Issue-Admission Result",
        "",
        "Likely merge or expand existing REG-004 rather than create a new issue. The structural concern is not ordinary policy disagreement over an agency's mission; it is whether the executive can use RIFs, transfers, funding freezes, website/system shutdowns, or program terminations to make a congressionally created agency unable to perform statutory duties without Congress first repealing or restructuring it.",
        "",
        "## New Issue / Merge Recommendation",
        "",
        "Merge recommendation: source-develop under REG-004 and decide during adjudication whether REG-004 should become a developed proposal on statutory agency-continuity safeguards. Do not create a separate USAID-only or Education-only issue unless source development shows a distinct remedial architecture.",
        "",
        "## Current Disposition at Intake",
        "",
        "Adjudicate HOR-018 after collecting primary statutory and litigation records. Likely remedy fields include agency-continuity floors, transfer/reorganization limits, anti-nullification rules, RIF review, appropriations/impoundment safeguards, preservation of statutory program capacity, and expedited judicial review.",
        "",
        "## Sources / Next Source Need",
        "",
        "Sources reviewed: [White House EO 14242 directing Education closure steps](https://www.whitehouse.gov/presidential-actions/2025/03/improving-education-outcomes-by-empowering-parents-states-and-communities/); [Education Department RIF press release](https://www.ed.gov/about/news/press-release/us-department-of-education-initiates-reduction-force); [Supreme Court docket in McMahon v. New York, No. 24A1203](https://www.supremecourt.gov/search.aspx?filename=/docket/docketfiles/html/public/24a1203.html); [Guardian on Rubio announcement terminating 83% of USAID programs](https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2025/mar/10/marco-rubio-usaid-funding); [Washington Post on formal USAID dismantling move](https://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/2025/03/28/trump-usaid-abolish-earthquake-congress/). Next source need: Department of Education Organization Act, Foreign Assistance Act/USAID statutory authorities, appropriations and impoundment records, RIF notices, transfer memoranda, district-court orders, appellate merits posture, and any GAO/IG findings.",
        "",
        "## Confidence",
        "",
        "High for overlap with REG-004; medium-high for final remedial design pending primary-record review",
        "",
        "## Workflow Note",
        "",
        "This GitHub issue was the public workflow wrapper for the horizon candidate. The repository remains the substantive record."
      ]
