      "issue_body_html": "<h2>Disposition<\/h2>\n<p><strong>Integrated into <a href=\"https://github.com/Thorncrag/ARRP/blob/main/areas/EMERG/issues/EMERG-003.md\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">EMERG-003: Emergency Economic Powers as a Substitute for Legislation<\/a> on July 14, 2026.<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>This issue is preserved as the permanent HOR-030 horizon intake record. The adjudicated disposition is also recorded in the <a href=\"https://github.com/Thorncrag/ARRP/blob/main/framework/logs/HORIZON_SCAN_LOG.md\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Horizon Scan Log<\/a>.<\/p>\n<h2>Original Concern<\/h2>\n<p>Executive use of sanctions, visa restrictions, and diplomatic pressure to isolate or dismantle the International Criminal Court, including possible action against judges, prosecutors, witnesses, supporting organizations, private service providers, and cooperating states.<\/p>\n<h2>Adjudication Finding<\/h2>\n<p>The political merits of ICC membership, jurisdiction, recognition, or cooperation are outside ARRP. The repairable and generalizable defect is executive use of general emergency-economic and immigration authority to establish a major sanctions category that Congress did not specifically enact.<\/p>\n<p>ASPA establishes substantial congressional noncooperation policy but does not generally authorize property and entry sanctions against ICC-associated persons; it also preserves limited assistance related to foreign nationals in Ukraine. H.R. 23 would have supplied specific property and entry sanctions, but it did not become law. Executive Order 14203 then created a functionally similar discretionary program through IEEPA, the National Emergencies Act, and immigration authority.<\/p>\n<p>EMERG-003 is therefore the correct existing home. A separate ICC-specific proposal would duplicate the emergency-powers defect and risk making the project advocate a contested international-law position.<\/p>\n<h2>Implemented Remedy Direction<\/h2>\n<p>The <a href=\"https://github.com/Thorncrag/ARRP/blob/main/legislation/EMERG-003.md\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">first statutory draft<\/a> requires a direct and substantial nexus to the declared threat and specific congressional authorization before property, transaction, entry, or visa sanctions may rest substantially on covered adjudicative activity. It preserves sanctions based on independently wrongful conduct and does not decide any ICC membership, jurisdiction, cooperation, funding, surrender, or case-outcome question.<\/p>\n<h2>Next Step<\/h2>\n<p>Conduct T1 review of IEEPA scope, INA coordination, D.D.C. review, classified records, transition relief, and implementation cost under EMERG-003. Revisit HOR-030 only if later action reveals a distinct institutional defect not addressable through emergency-authority limits or HOR-026&#x27;s international-commitment framework.<\/p>\n<h2>Key Sources<\/h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"https://www.federalregister.gov/documents/full_text/html/2025/02/12/2025-02612.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Executive Order 14203<\/a><\/li><li><a href=\"https://www.congress.gov/bill/119th-congress/house-bill/23/text\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">H.R. 23<\/a><\/li><li><a href=\"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%28title%3A22+section%3A7423+edition%3Aprelim%29\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">22 U.S.C. § 7423<\/a><\/li><li><a href=\"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?edition=prelim&amp;num=0&amp;req=granuleid%3AUSC-prelim-title22-section7433\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">22 U.S.C. § 7433<\/a><\/li><li><a href=\"https://ofac.treasury.gov/sanctions-programs-and-country-information/international-criminal-court-related-sanctions\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">OFAC ICC-related sanctions program<\/a><\/li><li><a href=\"https://www.investing.com/news/world-news/trump-administration-launches-effort-to-isolate-international-criminal-court-4788814\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Reuters, July 13, 2026<\/a><\/li><\/ul>",
