        "decision": "Promoted to an active monitoring Horizon candidate; static HOR ID tracked through GitHub issue #274. Promotion does not admit a proposal or take a position on the preferred level of ESA protection.",
        "integrated_into": "Provisionally Cross-cutting; duplicate and boundary review with administrative-law, judicial-review, and science-integrity records.",
        "rationale": "16 U.S.C. § 1533 deliberately distinguishes listing determinations, which rely solely on the best scientific and commercial data available, from critical-habitat designations and exclusions, for which Congress authorized consideration of economic, national-security, and other relevant impacts subject to an extinction safeguard. The Department of the Interior announcement describes finalized changes in both categories. An exercise of discretion Congress supplied, or a disagreement with environmental policy, is not itself an ARRP institutional defect.",
        "follow_up": "Monitor final Federal Register text and implementing guidance; any merits or controlling threshold litigation; any listing or critical-habitat decision that may apply economic considerations outside the statutory role; and evidence of difficult-to-repair loss before ordinary review. Retire the candidate if the final materials remain within delegated discretion and ordinary review is adequate; otherwise reassess whether a distinct, generalizable remedy is justified.",
