      "needs_monitoring": false,
      "created_at": "2026-07-19T00:42:53Z",
      "updated_at": "2026-07-19T00:42:53Z",
      "issue_body_html": "<h2>Canonical Project Page<\/h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"https://github.com/Thorncrag/ARRP/blob/main/framework/logs/HORIZON_SCAN_LOG.md\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Horizon Scan Log<\/a><\/li><li><a href=\"https://github.com/Thorncrag/ARRP/blob/main/areas/EMERG/README.md\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Provisional emergency-powers area<\/a><\/li><li>Horizon ID: <code>HOR-040<\/code><\/li><li>Preliminary intake provenance: <code>INTAKE-GAP-008<\/code><\/li><\/ul>\n<h2>Workflow Purpose<\/h2>\n<p>This issue is the public workflow wrapper for an ARRP Horizon candidate concerning safeguards for broad presidential tariff delegations outside IEEPA. Promotion does not admit a proposal or take a position on the merits of any tariff policy.<\/p>\n<h2>Institutional Question<\/h2>\n<p>Trade statutes may permit a President to impose, escalate, negotiate, or selectively waive economically consequential tariffs or duty treatment through broad national-security, balance-of-payments, trade-adjustment, or program-eligibility findings. The candidate asks whether the statutory criteria, procedures, duration limits, reporting, congressional controls, and judicial review adequately constrain difficult-to-reverse unilateral action.<\/p>\n<h2>Existing Coverage and Counterargument<\/h2>\n<p>EMERG-003 owns IEEPA-based economic action. This candidate concerns section 232, section 201, section 301, GSP, AGOA, and other non-IEEPA authorities and must be compared with EMERG-001, JUD-011, and the project&#x27;s spending and congressional-oversight proposals.<\/p>\n<p>The strongest counterargument is that Congress deliberately enacted these delegations, often required agency investigations or findings, retained power to amend them, and may rationally prefer executive flexibility in foreign trade and national security. Some authorities may already contain adequate safeguards.<\/p>\n<h2>Supporting Record<\/h2>\n<p>Representative source IDs: <code>SRC-1198<\/code>, <code>SRC-1199<\/code>, <code>SRC-1205<\/code>, <code>SRC-1206<\/code>, and <code>SRC-1207<\/code> in the project source registry. The directive catalog retains the complete supporting cluster.<\/p>\n<h2>Next Step<\/h2>\n<p>Conduct a statute-by-statute safeguard, remedy, and merger analysis. Determine which authorities are adequately constrained, whether the remaining concern belongs inside EMERG-003, and whether any distinct trade-authority remedy is justified.<\/p>",
