      "issue_body_html": "<h2>Canonical Project Page<\/h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"https://github.com/Thorncrag/ARRP/blob/main/framework/logs/HORIZON_SCAN_LOG.md\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Horizon Scan Log<\/a><\/li><li><a href=\"https://github.com/Thorncrag/ARRP/blob/main/areas/REG/README.md\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Provisional regulatory-integrity area<\/a><\/li><li>Horizon ID: <code>HOR-044<\/code><\/li><li>Preliminary intake provenance: <code>INTAKE-GAP-012<\/code><\/li><\/ul>\n<h2>Workflow Purpose<\/h2>\n<p>This issue is the public workflow wrapper for an ARRP Horizon candidate concerning the statutory framework for presidential cross-border infrastructure permits. Promotion does not admit a proposal or take a position on any particular pipeline, railway, bridge, or other facility.<\/p>\n<h2>Institutional Question<\/h2>\n<p>Cross-border facilities may be approved through a presidential permitting system created substantially by executive practice, without uniform statutory criteria or procedures and with some presidential decisions treated as outside ordinary Administrative Procedure Act review. The candidate asks whether facility types lacking express statutory authority require clearer criteria, notice, consultation, findings, records, and review.<\/p>\n<h2>Existing Coverage and Counterargument<\/h2>\n<p>REG-006 concerns presidential control of agency rulemaking and legal positions; FED and HER records concern state, tribal, environmental, or property interests. The review must also compare REG-003, FED-002, FED-004, HER-001, HOR-031, JUD-011, and sector-specific statutes.<\/p>\n<p>The strongest counterargument is that longstanding executive practice and judicial decisions recognize substantial presidential foreign-affairs authority; Congress has repeatedly legislated around the permitting system; and state, tribal, environmental, safety, and sector-specific approvals may independently constrain domestic construction and operation.<\/p>\n<h2>Supporting Record<\/h2>\n<p>Representative source IDs: <code>SRC-1215<\/code>, <code>SRC-1216<\/code>, <code>SRC-1217<\/code>, <code>SRC-1218<\/code>, and <code>SRC-0931<\/code> in the project source registry. The directive catalog retains the complete supporting cluster.<\/p>\n<h2>Next Step<\/h2>\n<p>Build a facility-by-facility authority and review matrix; identify which facility types lack express statutory authority, what procedures and review presently apply, and whether any gap causes difficult-to-remedy harm before recommending admission, merger, or retirement.<\/p>",
