        "Cross-border facilities may be approved through a presidential permitting system created substantially by executive practice, without uniform statutory criteria or procedures and with some presidential decisions treated as outside ordinary Administrative Procedure Act review. The candidate asks whether facility types lacking express statutory authority require clearer criteria, notice, consultation, findings, records, and review.",
